HEADWORD: doorstop
<hw>door"stop`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Carp.)</fld>
<def>The block or strip of wood or similar material which stops, at the
right place, the shutting of a door; any object used to stop open doors
from moving.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>doorstopper</ent>⟦br⟧
